  "prompt": "Need career related advice. I am confused as to what should I go for right now. Please help?",
  "response": "Of course! To provide the best advice, it would help to know a bit more about your situation. Here are a few questions to consider:\n\n1. **Interests and Strengths**: What are your interests or passions? What subjects or activities do you find most engaging? Also, what skills do you think you excel at?\n\n2. **Education and Experience**: What level of education do you have, and what kind of experience (if any) do you have in a particular field or job?\n\n3. **Career Goals**: What are your short-term and long-term career goals? Are you looking for immediate employment, planning to pursue further education, or looking to switch careers?\n\n4. **Market Trends**: Are you aware of job market trends in your area or the areas you're interested in? Certain industries may have more opportunities than others.\n\n5. **Work Environment**: What kind of work environment do you thrive in? Do you prefer teamwork or independent work? A fast-paced workplace or a more relaxed one?\n\n6. **Work-Life Balance**: What are your priorities in terms of work-life balance, salary expectations, job stability, etc.?\n\nOnce you provide more details, I can help you explore potential career paths or provide tailored advice!",
